The test file currently has 3 tests. The user says they've already handled test changes, so I should only modify the source code. Let me now look at the full constructor to understand all the builder properties that configure HttpClient:

The key insight is that the constructor at line 77-85 builds the `HttpClient`:

```java
HttpClient.Builder clientBuilder =
        HttpClient.newBuilder().connectTimeout(timeout).version(httpVersion);
if (builder.executor != null) {
    clientBuilder.executor(builder.executor);
}
if (sslContext != null) {
    clientBuilder.sslContext(sslContext);
}
httpClient = clientBuilder.build();
```

The fix is to add a `httpClient` field to the Builder and if it's provided, use it directly instead of building one.

